Diagnosis.
Dorsum covered with decumbent to suberect brown clavate scales (
Figures 2, 3
); lacking long setae on lateral regions of elytra. Antennae short, not reaching posterior margin of pronotum when directed backwards (
Figures 4, 5
). Pronotum with lateral margins subparallel, anterior angles produced anteriorly.

