Comparing the distributions of male rostrum distal width, female pronotum width and female elytral width, shows some overlap between the first two traits (
Figure 23
), but minimal overlap between male rostrum distal width and female elytral width (
Figure 23
). A total of 43% of males had rostral widths that were greater than the female with the narrowest pronotum, while 75% of females had pronotal widths that were less than the widest male rostrum (
Figure 24
). The top 20% of males had rostrum widths that were wider than the pronotum width of 50% of females.
